<br>
I agree it is frustrating to have a caster loose their pet to enrage, but I don't sweat it. It is my job to turn off attack when I get the enrage message so I don't die. If the pet isn't behind the mob for what ever reason, it is the pets owners own fault if they don't back their pet off during enrage.<br>
<br>
Yes, pets are not pc, but they are run by players and part of the fun of being a pet class is figuring out where you need to set your pet, not getting the tank to figure it out for you. <p>Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
