<br>
If I can give the pets the back of any exp mob, I will. If the pet can backstab, it becomes a bit more important to me. If the mobs running around and being a general pain to position, I might not be able to do so.<br>
<br>
On raid level encounters... I'm not going to swap an about to enrage mob. Sorry, but your pet is competing with all the melee that are on the back, if he's not. If this mob has been knocked across the room and back 8 times... You may or may not get the back. <br>
<br>
Someone said that if the mob enrages, your quadding pet is dead before his HP bar updates?<br>
<br>
I duel wield 18 delay weapons, generally. I generally have at least VoG, and 36% item haste. I laugh when people call rage in channel because I'd be dead by the time I read it. And I rarely take much, if any, enrage damage.<br>
<br>
Really, it works better if both classes make the effort. The tank positions it if he can. The pet class backs off if he can't.<br>
<br>
Warrior, really, is just attack, kick, taunt, same as mage is just /pet attack, nuke, DS. It's knowing when and where to press those buttons that seperates the wheat from the chaff. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17853"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://photo5.matchnet.com/beta/2002/10/15/13205296.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior>The Steel Warrior</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena>The Arena</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.steelwarrior.org">The Steel Warrior website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
